The changing TC trajectories are consistent with findings from other
of methodologies, including statistical models, stalagmite chronology,
global best-track data and reanalysis data, and overwash deposits (30
33). Further, ref. 34 noted a poleward shift in the tracks of 21
extratropical cyclones simulated from CMIP5 models and indicated
that changes to storm location and intensity likely combine to impact
future surge events at the Battery, similar to our finding for TCs.
